NetStat
=======

29-Aug-2009
~~~~~~~~~~~
Now using a daemon to track usage, communicating via DBus.

04-May-2009
~~~~~~~~~~~
More work trying to track usage.

29-Aug-2008
~~~~~~~~~~~
Fix bugs in the loading of saved usage.

26-Jul-2008
~~~~~~~~~~~
Handle usage in the case where the system has been re-booted.

25-May-2008
~~~~~~~~~~~
Track bandwidth usage.

29-Apr-2006
~~~~~~~~~~~
Added i18n support.
Changed some deprecated code.

21-Nov-2005
~~~~~~~~~~~
Use newer menu system.

03-May-2005 (0.1.1)
~~~~~~~~~~~
Better scaling of maximum in chart display.
Stop updating socket windows when they are destroyed!
Better lookup of IP addresses on Linux.

23-Apr-2005
~~~~~~~~~~~
Require ROX-Lib 2.0.0.

03-Apr-2005
~~~~~~~~~~~
Better AppRun/AppletRun as suggested by Thomas Leonard.

17-Mar-2005
~~~~~~~~~~~
Improved selection of font scaling.

15-Jan-2005 (0.1.0)
~~~~~~~~~~~
Added alternative display using strip charts.

0.0.12
------
Use stock icons in the menu.
Colour levels for byte count now configurable.

0.0.11
------
Get the byte count if we can and display that in preference to the packet 
count.
Change to way arrows are drawn and labeled.
Use new findrox.

0.0.10
------
Use new InfoWin interface.
Fix AppRun/AppletRun for Zero Install.

0.0.9
-----
Italian translation of AppInfo provided by Yuri Bongiorno.
Better platform test provided by Chris Arndt.

0.0.8
-----
Added window size option.  Work on apparent memory leak.
Menu options to view active/all sockets.

0.0.7
-----
More interesting display if interface not configured.

0.0.6
-----
Use longs to store stats, not ints (Thomas Leonard).

0.0.5
-----
Fix bug that broke Linux support.

0.0.4
-----
Make better use of ROX-Lib2, including options window.  Support Solaris.

0.0.3
-----
Reap the dead processes when we run the connect program.

0.0.2
-----
First release.
